  /// Res, Overflow = umul.with_overflow X, C1
  /// Try to fold "Overflow || (Res u> C2)" into "X u> floor(C2 / C1)".
  /// This is valid because:
  /// - If there's no overflow, then Res = X * C1, so Res u> C2 is X u> floor(C2 / C1)
  /// - If there is overflow, then X * C1 wrapped around, which means X was large
  ///   enough to overflow. For unsigned multiplication, overflow || (Res u> C2)
  ///   is true exactly when X > floor(C2 / C1).
